@pdeva ok, my previous comment was wrong. To execute 10K queries per min, each query should take at most 6 ms if all they are run in sequential. But, Druid is capable of running queries in parallel, so this shouldn't be a problem. And this is why I said the number of queries matters. How many queries are you running? 10K queries per minute?

